Name: Note
Desc_: Data is updated daily by about 4 p.m. and includes cases reported through the previous day.

Name: Note
Desc_: The number of cases includes people who have had a test that indicated they were positive for COVID-19. The number of cases also includes epidemiologically-linked cases -- or cases where public health epidemiologists have determined that infection is highly likely because a person exhibited symptoms and had close contact with someone who tested positive. The number of epidemiologically-linked cases represents a very small portion of the reported cases.

Name: Note
Desc_: Total people tested may not include all negative results. Testing data excludes serology and only counts PCR.

Name: Note
Desc_: A person is counted once in the number of People Tested. A person is counted once each day they are tested in the number of Test Encounters.
